{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808/events","html_url":"https://github.com/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808","id":1390267596,"node_id":"I_kwDOCpMuHc5S3czM","number":808,"title":"[Julia] `visit_Cast` does not recognize arrays properly","user":{"login":"lucifer1004","id":13583761,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTgzNzYx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13583761?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004","html_url":"https://github.com/lucifer1004","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2022-09-29T05:16:45Z","updated_at":"2022-09-30T04:59:31Z","closed_at":"2022-09-30T04:59:30Z","author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"```fortran\r\nprogram s\r\n   integer :: a(10)\r\n   real(8) :: b(10)\r\n   a = 2\r\n   b = 0.2\r\n   b(2) = 100.2\r\n   a = int(b)\r\n   print *, a(1:2)\r\nend program\r\n```\r\nemits (intrinsics omitted, #807 applied)\r\n\r\n```julia\r\nfunction main()\r\n    local a = Array{Int32, 1}(undef, 10)\r\n    local b = Array{Float64, 1}(undef, 10)\r\n    a .= 2\r\n    b .=   2.00000000000000011e-01\r\n    b[2] =   1.00200000000000003e+02\r\n    a .= trunc(Int32, b)\r\n    println(a[1:1:2])\r\nend\r\n\r\nmain()\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe problem is that `trunc(Int32, b)` does not work because `b` is an `Array` and broadcast needs to be used.\r\n\r\nThe current implementation tries to figure this out by calling `ASRUtils::is_array()` on `x.m_type` in `visit_Cast`\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/lfortran/lfortran/blob/4fb3fd0f8512451cf1d73368c0a77d9f8e11881f/src/libasr/codegen/asr_to_julia.cpp#L1458\r\n\r\nBut it seems that this did not work in the example above.","closed_by":{"login":"lucifer1004","id":13583761,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTgzNzYx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13583761?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004","html_url":"https://github.com/lucifer1004","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lucifer1004/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/808/timeline","performed_via_github_